      <item>
        <title>Why not using Grunt.js?</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;The answer is very simple: &lt;em&gt;i need to be more simple as possible&lt;/em&gt;.
&lt;strong&gt;Grunt.js&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Node.js&lt;/strong&gt; are amazing tools, but i so simple as Jekyll is.
You can use &lt;strong&gt;SCSS&lt;/strong&gt;, on &lt;code&gt;assets&lt;/code&gt; folder, but is totally optional. The &lt;em&gt;CSS&lt;/em&gt; files in use are on &lt;code&gt;stylesheets&lt;/code&gt; folder.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
